"""
Bio.motifs.minimal Test Suite - Codon Implementation

Comprehensive test suite for MEME minimal format parser ported from BioPython 
to Codon, a high-performance Python compiler for computational biology.

Codon Adaptations Made:
- Replaced Python unittest framework with custom assertion functions
- Used @test decorators instead of unittest.TestCase methods
- Simplified exception handling (removed specific exception type checking)
- Used literal tolerance values for floating point comparisons
- Replaced complex file I/O with string-based parsing
- Added explicit type handling for cross-language compatibility
- Maintained BioPython API compatibility while optimizing for Codon's static compilation
- Used manual string manipulation instead of advanced Python string methods

Classes Tested:
- Record: MEME format results container with motif indexing and iteration
- Motif: Motif representation with counts, metadata, and background frequencies
- Module functions: read(), _read_version(), _read_alphabet(), _read_background(), etc.

Test Coverage:
- MEME file format parsing (version, alphabet, background frequencies)
- Motif parsing (names, statistics, letter-probability matrices)
- Record operations (indexing by name/number, iteration, length)
- Error handling (invalid formats, missing data, malformed input)
- Edge cases (empty files, single motifs, RNA vs DNA alphabets)
- Integration testing of complete parsing pipeline

30+ test cases validate Codon-compiled MEME minimal format parsing functionality 
for high-performance computational biology applications.
"""

